{{DISPLAYTITLE:<span style="font-family:Times New Roman; color:#ffffff; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #4C75B6">Level 806: "Back to School"</span>}}
<div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Times New Roman; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;">
<div style="background-color:rgba(0,215,0,0.224); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Times New Roman; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Description</font></div>
'''Level 806, commonly referred to as "Back to School"''', is a modern school that stretches infinitely in all directions. An insurmountable number of classrooms, offices, and libraries span within this level.

{{Blurimage|file=School_hallway_img1.jpg|caption=The first known image of this level.}}

The floors typically consist of colored oak wood, and the walls are mostly made out of either indestructible bricks or concrete. Soft mellow music flows through the level, with an unknown point of origin. The scent varies place to place, though the smell of new books and wood will cover most areas. The temperature is relatively hot, from 25℃ to around 31℃, although the level still occasionally provides a cool breeze.

The level's layout is often predictable, with minimal non-Euclidean properties found throughout '''Level 806'''. The structure of the school is organized and can be mapped easily. Direction in this level is also intuitive to follow with many maps posted throughout this level, which avoids confusion and ultimately getting lost.

{{Blurimage|caption=High school classroom.|align=left|file=highschoolclassroom_img2.jpg}}

When exploring, '''Classrooms''' are usually the first to be stumbled upon. Classrooms, when unoccupied, typically resemble modern American high school classrooms, though variants exist, like elementary ones. Entering any of these classrooms will inflict a strong sense of nostalgia through some kind of anomaly, especially in elementary classrooms.

All of the Classrooms' design highly vary due to them being based off of memory. Specifically, it is when a wanderer inhabits a classroom. The room somehow reads the wanderer's memory, and designs the classroom based off of it. It becomes eclectic when another wanderer decides to inhabit that specific classroom as well. So far, this is the only section of '''Level 806''' to heavily use non-Euclidean properties.

'''Offices''' are often to be spotted as well; these offices consist of randomly segmented cubicles. The cubicles are made out of grey concrete, but some are also made from galvanized steel. The area for each cubicle is measured to be 4 meters by 5 meters. Inside, it always contains an L-shaped desk, multiple steel drawers, an ergonomic chair, a PC setup, a microwave, and some potted plants. Offices can be heavily utilized as the PCs inside are fully functional and many stationeries appear inside steel drawers. Vending machines<ref>They host a variety of pre-packaged meals and drinks, and these never expire.</ref> and water dispensers can also be found throughout this section. These vending machines are '''Level 806's''' main food source.

Meeting rooms seldomly appear inside Offices, and are usually out-of-place or isolated. In the middle of these meeting rooms, a large wooden table can always be found. Numerous office chairs encircle the table, and a whiteboard supported by steel on the front side of the table. Plastic drawers in shades of grey are also typically spotted. Whiteboards occasionally have information about how to survive other levels, making it useful to wanderers who are in '''Level 806''' for a quick stay.

Sometimes, abnormally large venues can be stumbled upon when traversing '''Level 806''', and they appear less often than offices or classrooms. These are '''Facilities''', and they consist of libraries or pools.

{{Blurimage|caption=The pools.|file=pools806.jpg}}

'''Libraries''' contains large, towering bookshelves, with an abundance of books residing in its counters. It is made out of maple wood, with it having a musty smell. These bookshelves often interconnect or collide, which makes layouts of this section very messy and thus is hard to navigate. Deeper regions may occasionally have cracks appearing on bookshelves and can cause collapse at any given time. Due to this, it is recommended not to explore into deep regions of this area. 

'''Pools''' are located in a venue. It has two or three pools, and are always separated and have equal size to each other. The pool walls and floors are laid with ceramic tiles, akin to [[Level 37]]'s. Wooden benches are commonly seen alongside pools and are placed orderly. The venue's floor is made of wooden boards, and lacks splinters for safety. The water inside the pools posess an unusually deep blue color, which is reported to contain [[Level 330]] compounds, though extensive research has led to reducing returns.

<div style="background-color:rgba(0,215,0,0.224); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Times New Roman; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Entities</font></div>
Only [[Facelings]] inhabit this level. The Tranquility Effect is present, and all facelings encountered are docile to wanderers and are unable to attack.

<br><div style="background-color:rgba(0,215,0,0.224); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Times New Roman; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Anomalies</font></div>
===<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">Kairos</div>===
Kairos is an anomaly only found in '''Level 806'''. Kairos is derived from the Greek word καιρός, which means "critical/opportune moment". This anomaly affects when wanderers can arrive at this level. These dates allowing entrance happen annually, and accepting entrance into this level is generally during American school breaks in the Frontrooms,
* March 20<sup>th</sup> to April 1<sup>st</sup>,
* June 16<sup>th</sup> to August 6<sup>th</sup>, 
*and December 23<sup>rd</sup> to January 9<sup>th</sup>.<br>
After these dates, wanderers are disbarred from entering this level or exiting this level. No-clipping to exit this level will become nigh impossible to do. Even if one happens to somehow do it, it will most likely glitch one into [[The Void|nothing]].

===<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">Student Mentality</div>===
After staying in '''Level 806''' for prolonged amounts of time, one may start to feel more motivated to research about a specific topic or concentrate on something for an extended amount of time. Attention span will also increase, and wanderers with ADHD may be magically cured for unknown reasons. The feeling of hunger and thirst will decrease exponentially even after a long time without eating. Due to this, it is highly advised to track time and when one ate or drank.
<div style="background-color:rgba(0,215,0,0.224); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Times New Roman; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Outposts</font></div>
===<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">The Students of Level 806</div>===

*Very friendly, helpful, and open to trade.
*Consists of roughly 500+ members.
*Located in classrooms, most near The Center.
*Accepts new members.

<div style="background-color:rgba(0,215,0,0.224); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Times New Roman; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Discovery</font></div>
<blockquote>On August 1st, 1993, this level was discovered by a M.E.G. staff member named Darrel Tugger in an effort to find and inhabit safer levels to aid the lack of safe levels during the time. Ever since discovery and exploration, it skyrocketed in popularity, and many people started to migrate to this level.</blockquote>

<div style="background-color:rgba(0,215,0,0.224); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Times New Roman; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">The Center</font></div>
Wanderers always spawn in an area called '''The Center''' after [[No-Clipping|no-clipping]] from other levels. It is heavily suspected to be the origin of this level, and is theorized that the level is ever-expanding and started to expand from The Center. This has intrigued many wanderers, group officials, theorists alike into thinking: "What is possibly the space beyond where the level has not materialized yet?"

Some say it rests near [[Uncharted Territory]], some say [[The Broken]] has to do with the creation of this level. But who knows? It may forever be a mystery.
{{Login|username=isTerrariaTuff|organization=M.E.G.|num=67|password=67terrariasita|body=
But perhaps... there's more to the story. There ''always'' is. Thank our dear main picture-taker for dropping this useful information for us.
{{Collapse|initial=+ File 1|final=- File 1|body=<big><center>

'''Level 806'''.

Theorists say it is a venture, into the depths of enigma.

A rumor that flows around, yet for so long unconfirmed.

An ever-expanding level, many leads searched but with diminishing results.

To truly find out, one must walk amounts comparable to eons.

A rigorous find indeed, even multiple gods struggle.

Many others see it as fruitless. But I see it as a worthy challenge.

So from the Center, I began walking.

I walked, and walked, without a stop.

Though the pain of continued walking is indescribably agonizing;

I continue, without a doubt, even when in the abyss of uncertainty and hopelessness.

Near the end, I felt a resolution.

At the time, I wasn't sure what, surely something was going to end.

Then I saw it.

Finally, after every inconvenience, every mishap...

Case solved.
[[File:calamitatedfortunation.png|link=|center|700px]]

Now, the only thought I have left is...

Does it have any relations, or ties to [[The Void]]?

That is a question to ponder.
</center></big>

<div style="text-align:center;"><small>- unknown note, most likely written by [[Entity 1|The Cameraman]]</small>
